# Documentation updates

When making changes, update documentation intentionally:

- **README.md** — stable public-facing information only (positioning, status, high-level feature lists, links). Do not bloat with implementation noise or daily notes.
- **CHANGELOG.md** — meaningful user-facing, operational, or security changes (under Unreleased until a release tag).
- **docs/dev-log.md** — daily build progress; roll up to weekly/monthly summaries per docs/docs-maintenance.md.
- **docs/product-decisions.md** — locked product rules from Rhys / planning Q&A.
- **docs/product-roadmap.md** — future ideas and non-goals.
- **docs/docs-maintenance.md** — doc workflow reference.

Do not duplicate product-decisions or roadmap content into README.

Never commit secrets or real env values in docs.
